    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Agree with @0xPhaze on syntax here, the different `--debug` syntax always trips me up. I often find myself re-running a single test to iron out errors, then trying to jump in the debugger by just adding `--debug` to my last command. So for example using `forge test --mt testX --mc ContractA --debug` should work but error if the combination of matchers gives anything except exactly 1 test (would be nice for it log all the matches in that case too)\r\n\r\n",
